The President of the Nigerian Senate, Ahmad Lawan on Friday maintained that President Muhammadu Buhari will continue to receive the backing of the National Assembly in order to move the country forward. According to Lawan who spoke in Akure, the Ondo State capital while meeting with the state governor, Oluwarotimi Akeredolu, the members of 9th National Assembly are ready to give their all to the growth of the country irrespective of their political leaning. Lawan alongside some principal officers of the Senate and the senators from the state were in the state to visit the ailing senator representing the Southern Senatorial district of the state, Nicholas Tofowomo. Recall that Tofowomo as well some chieftains of the Peoples Democratic Party were involved in an auto crash two months ago. During a stopover at the Government House to also visit Governor Akeredolu who is equally recuperating from an undisclosed ailment, Lawan assured Nigerians that the 9th National Assembly would ensure a better country. “We will continue to give legislative support to the Federal government to improve the situations in the country. “Our political Parties platform notwithstanding, we are working for the betterment of the country. Party affiliation doesn’t matter. This 9th assembly is one united family. He appealed to Nigerians to be patient with the present administration as efforts are on to ensure that the dividend of democracy gets to every citizenry. According to him, the present administration is working assiduously to ensure the security situation, economy, and employment opportunities improve for the betterment of Nigerians. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.